1
00:00:27,320 --> 00:00:28,920
What are you thinking about?

2
00:00:30,440 --> 00:00:31,350
The exam results

3
00:00:31,350 --> 00:00:32,549
are about to come out.

4
00:00:33,560 --> 00:00:34,560
Feeling nervous?

5
00:00:35,920 --> 00:00:36,720
It's alright.

6
00:00:40,560 --> 00:00:41,670
I got you a gift.

7
00:00:45,390 --> 00:00:47,990
To celebrate our graduation
from high school.

8
00:00:55,520 --> 00:00:56,030
You...

9
00:00:56,750 --> 00:00:58,010
Where did you get this?

10
00:00:59,640 --> 00:01:00,320
I bought it.

11
00:01:01,430 --> 00:01:02,320
Bought it?

12
00:01:02,920 --> 00:01:04,280
Where did you get the money?

13
00:01:04,280 --> 00:01:05,209
I made it myself.

14
00:01:06,120 --> 00:01:07,070
During the holidays at home,

15
00:01:07,070 --> 00:01:08,600
I picked up some new skills.

16
00:01:13,510 --> 00:01:15,200
I didn't expect that, Su Muxin.

17
00:01:15,200 --> 00:01:16,600
you're quite something.

18
00:01:29,760 --> 00:01:31,120
Then I'll keep this.

19
00:01:31,870 --> 00:01:32,470
Yours.

20
00:01:35,940 --> 00:01:37,840
[Muxin]

21
00:01:40,430 --> 00:01:42,080
[Qu Tong]

22
00:03:38,120 --> 00:03:41,430
[Beloved]

23
00:03:41,930 --> 00:03:44,400
[Episode 8: Who Are You Really?]

24
00:03:48,079 --> 00:03:48,800
Wang.

25
00:03:49,960 --> 00:03:51,040
What's the matter?

26
00:03:52,310 --> 00:03:52,960
Mr. Fu.

27
00:03:53,710 --> 00:03:54,630
It's still about

28
00:03:54,630 --> 00:03:56,520
the original vehicle records.

29
00:03:57,630 --> 00:03:58,400
What does this matter

30
00:03:58,400 --> 00:03:59,710
have to do with you?

31
00:04:00,360 --> 00:04:01,590
I have the originals.

32
00:04:02,310 --> 00:04:04,710
You don't need to worry
about these things.

33
00:04:06,590 --> 00:04:08,040
So, this car...

34
00:04:08,430 --> 00:04:10,290
has it been you using it all along?

35
00:04:11,120 --> 00:04:12,750
I said, regarding some matters,

36
00:04:12,750 --> 00:04:14,680
aren't you meddling a bit too much?

37
00:04:15,080 --> 00:04:16,279
No matter who uses it—

38
00:04:16,480 --> 00:04:17,070
I use it,

39
00:04:17,089 --> 00:04:18,510
but it's not you.

40
00:04:24,920 --> 00:04:25,690
Did someone

41
00:04:25,720 --> 00:04:26,920
say something to you?

42
00:04:29,390 --> 00:04:30,720
No, no, no.

43
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:32,159
It's just that

44
00:04:32,190 --> 00:04:33,430
I can't keep things in.

45
00:04:33,430 --> 00:04:34,920
If you have a handle on it,

46
00:04:34,920 --> 00:04:35,830
then I won't ask further.

47
00:04:35,830 --> 00:04:38,070
Are you in Dongjiang?

48
00:04:38,560 --> 00:04:40,600
My hometown sent me
some local specialties.

49
00:04:40,600 --> 00:04:42,150
I'm in Yunzhou now.

50
00:04:42,310 --> 00:04:43,510
Can't return for now.

51
00:04:44,360 --> 00:04:45,530
I'm telling you,

52
00:04:45,560 --> 00:04:47,000
just keep it to yourself.

53
00:04:47,510 --> 00:04:48,790
Keep your mouth shut.

54
00:04:48,870 --> 00:04:49,510
Alright.

55
00:04:49,680 --> 00:04:50,390
That's it.

56
00:05:13,480 --> 00:05:15,270
One stack.

57
00:05:16,070 --> 00:05:17,800
Another stack.

58
00:05:19,960 --> 00:05:21,670
[Incoming Call from Qu Tong]

59
00:05:27,190 --> 00:05:27,750
Hello?

60
00:05:28,190 --> 00:05:29,000
Qu Tong.

61
00:05:29,480 --> 00:05:30,190
What's wrong?

62
00:05:30,190 --> 00:05:31,450
Do you need something?

63
00:05:32,720 --> 00:05:33,390
Wenjiang.

64
00:05:35,040 --> 00:05:37,300
I do have something I need your help with.

65
00:05:37,870 --> 00:05:38,400
Go ahead.

66
00:05:38,630 --> 00:05:40,070
As long as I can do it.

67
00:05:42,190 --> 00:05:44,120
You've already received 200,000.

68
00:05:46,270 --> 00:05:47,930
Give me the evidence you have.

69
00:05:53,120 --> 00:05:53,800
Hello?

70
00:05:55,480 --> 00:05:56,510
Can you hear me?

71
00:06:05,560 --> 00:06:07,090
What are you talking about?

72
00:06:07,230 --> 00:06:08,070
Why do I feel like

73
00:06:08,070 --> 00:06:09,530
I don't quite understand?

74
00:06:11,190 --> 00:06:13,150
Whether it's a joke, you know,

75
00:06:13,920 --> 00:06:15,150
and I know.

76
00:06:28,090 --> 00:06:31,450
[Call Ongoing]

77
00:06:39,470 --> 00:06:40,530
Really brilliant.

78
00:06:40,830 --> 00:06:42,390
Truly brilliant.

79
00:06:43,630 --> 00:06:44,390
Qu Tong.

80
00:06:45,120 --> 00:06:46,870
Someone who killed her husband

81
00:06:47,190 --> 00:06:48,650
really is something else.

82
00:06:52,560 --> 00:06:53,320
Fu Wenjiang.

83
00:06:55,640 --> 00:06:56,580
Where's the evidence?

84
00:06:56,580 --> 00:06:57,670
What evidence?

85
00:06:58,240 --> 00:06:59,900
You need to get this straight.

86
00:07:00,270 --> 00:07:01,530
Think back carefully.

87
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:03,360
What exactly did I say?

88
00:07:04,190 --> 00:07:05,040
200,000.

89
00:07:05,360 --> 00:07:06,730
If I don't get it,

90
00:07:06,870 --> 00:07:08,950
I'll hand the evidence to the police.

91
00:07:09,800 --> 00:07:11,120
But I never said

92
00:07:11,140 --> 00:07:12,940
I would give the evidence to you.

93
00:07:17,560 --> 00:07:18,430
You won't hand the evidence

94
00:07:18,430 --> 00:07:19,390
to the police.

95
00:07:21,600 --> 00:07:22,800
If you go down with me,

96
00:07:22,800 --> 00:07:24,260
it benefits no one, right?

97
00:07:28,160 --> 00:07:29,090
Don't forget...

98
00:07:30,610 --> 00:07:32,150
I already know it was you.

99
00:07:35,040 --> 00:07:36,040
If you want money,

100
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:40,070
I'll add another 100,000.

101
00:07:40,070 --> 00:07:40,930
How about that?

102
00:07:44,680 --> 00:07:45,390
Sure!

103
00:07:46,240 --> 00:07:47,500
Didn't I say it before?

104
00:07:47,830 --> 00:07:49,630
As long as it's your matter, Qu Tong,

105
00:07:49,630 --> 00:07:50,830
then it's my matter too.

106
00:07:50,830 --> 00:07:52,360
It's just one word from you.

107
00:07:54,730 --> 00:07:55,930
Where should we meet?

108
00:07:57,190 --> 00:07:58,680
We're family.

109
00:07:59,000 --> 00:07:59,630
Let's not

110
00:07:59,680 --> 00:08:00,750
go anywhere else.

111
00:08:00,870 --> 00:08:01,800
Let's meet at...

112
00:08:02,390 --> 00:08:03,720
the old warehouse of Zhuo'er.

113
00:08:03,720 --> 00:08:04,310
Alright?

114
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:05,870
See you later.

115
00:08:37,750 --> 00:08:39,280
Mentor, where are we going?

116
00:08:40,120 --> 00:08:42,390
Weren't you top of
your police academy class?

117
00:08:42,390 --> 00:08:43,270
Take a guess.

118
00:08:43,440 --> 00:08:45,190
Where do you think I want to go?

119
00:08:45,910 --> 00:08:48,030
There's still the matter of experience,
isn't there?

120
00:08:48,030 --> 00:08:49,130
In 1986,

121
00:08:50,150 --> 00:08:51,960
Su Mufan fell into the river and went missing.

122
00:08:51,960 --> 00:08:54,090
It was summer, the current was strong.

123
00:08:54,240 --> 00:08:56,640
He was blind, so it was hard to save himself.

124
00:08:57,630 --> 00:08:58,270
So?

125
00:08:58,320 --> 00:08:59,080
So...

126
00:08:59,910 --> 00:09:01,210
If he was alive,

127
00:09:01,870 --> 00:09:04,000
someone must have saved him back then.

128
00:09:04,790 --> 00:09:06,650
Maybe even sent him to a hospital.

129
00:09:07,670 --> 00:09:09,910
We'll go to Yunzhou County Hospital now,

130
00:09:09,910 --> 00:09:10,840
and try our luck.

131
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:11,550
Okay.

132
00:09:16,150 --> 00:09:17,370
I just want to ask,

133
00:09:17,480 --> 00:09:19,360
how can we meet Zhou Mi?

134
00:09:20,080 --> 00:09:20,670
Today,

135
00:09:20,670 --> 00:09:21,600
we must meet Zhou Mi.

136
00:09:21,600 --> 00:09:22,460
Officer Zhang.

137
00:09:22,550 --> 00:09:23,320
These two elders

138
00:09:23,320 --> 00:09:24,870
insist on seeing Captain Zhou.

139
00:09:24,870 --> 00:09:25,670
Her father, come here.

140
00:09:25,670 --> 00:09:26,600
Let's sit here.

141
00:09:26,670 --> 00:09:27,960
Let's sit here. Slowly.

142
00:09:27,960 --> 00:09:28,750
Slowly, slowly.

143
00:09:28,750 --> 00:09:29,750
Get up. You can't sit here.

144
00:09:29,750 --> 00:09:30,240
Slow down.

145
00:09:30,240 --> 00:09:30,910
Don't sit here.

146
00:09:30,910 --> 00:09:31,870
Elder, please get up.

147
00:09:31,870 --> 00:09:32,510
If we don't get to see Zhou Mi,

148
00:09:32,510 --> 00:09:33,090
we're not leaving!

149
00:09:33,090 --> 00:09:36,570
[Yunzhou No.1 Hospital]

150
00:09:33,270 --> 00:09:34,270
Check the medical records?

151
00:09:34,270 --> 00:09:35,320
At this hour,

152
00:09:35,390 --> 00:09:37,270
the records department is
already off duty.

153
00:09:37,270 --> 00:09:38,550
We're in a real hurry.

154
00:09:38,900 --> 00:09:40,200
It involves a major case.

155
00:09:40,200 --> 00:09:41,360
We need your cooperation.

156
00:09:41,360 --> 00:09:43,420
[Yunzhou No.1 Hospital]

157
00:09:41,960 --> 00:09:43,030
Alright, please wait a moment.

158
00:09:43,030 --> 00:09:44,430
I'll go ask the director.

159
00:09:44,930 --> 00:09:53,650
[Outpatient Department]

160
00:09:53,030 --> 00:09:53,630
Mr. Zhang.

161
00:09:55,030 --> 00:09:55,810
Listen,

162
00:09:55,910 --> 00:09:57,320
I've managed to calm them down for now.

163
00:09:57,320 --> 00:09:58,630
But I'm out of ideas for what comes next.

164
00:09:58,630 --> 00:10:00,000
You need to quickly
figure something out yourself.

165
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:01,550
Who told you to deal with them?

166
00:10:01,550 --> 00:10:04,180
[Focus on Medical Quality,
Put Patients First]

167
00:10:01,720 --> 00:10:02,510
Have you finished working on your cases?

168
00:10:02,510 --> 00:10:04,440
Don't have enough to do, is that it?

169
00:10:06,510 --> 00:10:08,440
How are you blaming me for this now?

170
00:10:09,510 --> 00:10:10,200
You—let me tell you,

171
00:10:10,200 --> 00:10:11,200
this is completely a case of

172
00:10:11,200 --> 00:10:13,060
“biting the hand that feeds you.”

173
00:10:13,120 --> 00:10:14,200
If this is your attitude,

174
00:10:13,180 --> 00:10:16,750
[Focus on Medical Quality,
Put Patients First]

175
00:10:14,870 --> 00:10:15,630
then nobody will be able to

176
00:10:15,630 --> 00:10:16,870
get along with you in the future.

177
00:10:16,870 --> 00:10:18,670
Hurry up and get them out of here.

178
00:10:19,320 --> 00:10:20,120
The Criminal Investigation Division

179
00:10:20,120 --> 00:10:22,120
isn't a place just anyone can enter.

180
00:10:22,510 --> 00:10:23,540
I mean, you, this...

181
00:10:23,540 --> 00:10:24,800
are you really a bit...

182
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:25,910
Zhang Dongliang.

183
00:10:25,910 --> 00:10:26,910
Cut the nonsense.

184
00:10:31,720 --> 00:10:32,520
Let me ask you.

185
00:10:33,110 --> 00:10:35,290
[Focus on Medical Quality,
Put Patients First]

186
00:10:33,550 --> 00:10:35,360
How's the vehicle investigation going?

187
00:10:35,360 --> 00:10:37,000
There’s been some progress.

188
00:10:37,150 --> 00:10:38,030
You were right.

189
00:10:38,030 --> 00:10:38,960
Zhuo'er Company

190
00:10:39,080 --> 00:10:40,910
does have a black Toyota Camry.

191
00:10:41,600 --> 00:10:42,790
But the vehicle requisition records

192
00:10:42,790 --> 00:10:43,920
were tampered with.

193
00:10:44,150 --> 00:10:44,910
The originals

194
00:10:44,910 --> 00:10:46,320
are with the Deputy General Manager of
Zhuo'er Company.

195
00:10:46,320 --> 00:10:47,120
Fu Wenjiang.

196
00:10:47,630 --> 00:10:48,360
The next step

197
00:10:48,360 --> 00:10:49,480
is to find Fu Wenjiang

198
00:10:49,480 --> 00:10:51,210
and get the originals from him.

199
00:10:51,720 --> 00:10:52,720
But he said

200
00:10:52,870 --> 00:10:54,600
he's busy at the factory in Yunzhou.

201
00:10:54,600 --> 00:10:56,910
and won't return to Dongjiang
in the next couple of days.

202
00:10:56,910 --> 00:10:57,480
Alright.

203
00:10:57,840 --> 00:10:59,120
Since he's in Yunzhou,

204
00:10:59,510 --> 00:11:00,440
then I'll check these couple of days,

205
00:11:00,440 --> 00:11:02,270
where he's been staying in Yunzhou.

206
00:11:02,270 --> 00:11:03,720
You—You listen to me.

207
00:11:03,750 --> 00:11:04,480
That's it.

208
00:11:04,790 --> 00:11:05,270
I—

209
00:11:09,840 --> 00:11:10,390
Next time,

210
00:11:10,390 --> 00:11:11,870
if you hang up on me again…

211
00:11:16,070 --> 00:11:16,790
Mentor!

212
00:11:17,530 --> 00:11:18,580
[Focus on Medical Quality,
Put Patients First]

213
00:11:19,750 --> 00:11:20,440
I just spoke with a nurse

214
00:11:20,440 --> 00:11:21,870
and found the head of
the emergency department.

215
00:11:21,870 --> 00:11:22,720
Found out since the 80s,

216
00:11:22,720 --> 00:11:23,910
he's been working at this hospital.

217
00:11:23,910 --> 00:11:25,640
Maybe he remembers something.

218
00:11:26,200 --> 00:11:26,630
Let's go!

219
00:11:26,630 --> 00:11:27,160
Let's go!

220
00:11:28,790 --> 00:11:30,020
Do you know how many patients

221
00:11:30,020 --> 00:11:31,280
I see every single day?

222
00:11:31,390 --> 00:11:32,790
Our place is by the river.

223
00:11:32,960 --> 00:11:33,530
Every year,

224
00:11:33,530 --> 00:11:35,480
many kids who fell in the water
are sent here.

225
00:11:35,480 --> 00:11:36,510
Especially back then,

226
00:11:36,510 --> 00:11:37,790
when there wasn't much supervision,

227
00:11:37,790 --> 00:11:39,030
many people went to play in the river,

228
00:11:39,030 --> 00:11:40,490
even for winter swimming.

229
00:11:40,960 --> 00:11:42,690
How could I possibly remember?

230
00:11:48,510 --> 00:11:49,510
He had a special trait.

231
00:11:49,510 --> 00:11:50,320
He was blind.

232
00:11:50,870 --> 00:11:52,240
Before he fell into the water,

233
00:11:52,240 --> 00:11:53,370
he had a head injury,

234
00:11:53,390 --> 00:11:55,050
causing him to lose his sight.

235
00:11:57,750 --> 00:11:59,080
There's no such person.

236
00:12:01,750 --> 00:12:03,410
You must remember something.

237
00:12:03,960 --> 00:12:04,720
What is it?

238
00:12:06,910 --> 00:12:08,000
What I remembered

239
00:12:08,030 --> 00:12:09,830
has nothing to do with your case.

240
00:12:11,320 --> 00:12:11,920
It's fine.

241
00:12:12,360 --> 00:12:13,120
Just tell us.

242
00:12:16,600 --> 00:12:17,800
You said a head injury

243
00:12:17,840 --> 00:12:19,320
caused blindness.

244
00:12:20,870 --> 00:12:22,270
That reminded me of a kid.

245
00:12:22,510 --> 00:12:24,510
The year I had just started working,

246
00:12:25,510 --> 00:12:26,440
also 1986,

247
00:12:26,440 --> 00:12:27,270
that summer.

248
00:12:28,550 --> 00:12:29,870
What happened? Who brought him in?

249
00:12:29,870 --> 00:12:30,630
Where's his family?

250
00:12:30,630 --> 00:12:31,240
I don't know.

251
00:12:31,240 --> 00:12:32,430
When we found him,
he was already at the hospital entrance.

252
00:12:32,430 --> 00:12:33,030
Young man!

253
00:12:33,360 --> 00:12:34,000
Young man!

254
00:12:34,510 --> 00:12:35,080
Young man!

255
00:12:35,080 --> 00:12:36,540
Can you hear me? Young man!

256
00:12:36,600 --> 00:12:37,270
Young man!

257
00:12:37,910 --> 00:12:38,970
Wake up, young man!

258
00:12:45,720 --> 00:12:47,850
But it had nothing to do with drowning.

259
00:12:49,240 --> 00:12:50,630
About this blind kid,

260
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:52,530
what else can you remember?

261
00:12:52,910 --> 00:12:53,600
Tell us.

262
00:12:56,240 --> 00:12:57,080
I remember...

263
00:12:57,120 --> 00:12:59,000
his name was entered incorrectly.

264
00:12:59,000 --> 00:13:00,150
When he was admitted,

265
00:13:00,150 --> 00:13:01,280
he was unconscious.

266
00:13:01,600 --> 00:13:02,480
The nurse found a student ID

267
00:13:02,480 --> 00:13:03,690
on him.

268
00:13:03,870 --> 00:13:04,750
with a photo.

269
00:13:05,080 --> 00:13:07,280
So they registered him under that name.

270
00:13:07,390 --> 00:13:08,630
After his mother arrived,

271
00:13:08,630 --> 00:13:10,550
at first she didn’t say it was wrong.

272
00:13:10,550 --> 00:13:11,320
Later,

273
00:13:11,480 --> 00:13:12,390
after some days,

274
00:13:12,390 --> 00:13:13,550
when he was about to be discharged,

275
00:13:13,550 --> 00:13:14,720
his mother came to me specially

276
00:13:14,720 --> 00:13:16,070
and said the name was registered wrong.

277
00:13:16,070 --> 00:13:17,530
She insisted I correct it.

278
00:13:18,480 --> 00:13:19,950
The two kids were twins.

279
00:13:20,240 --> 00:13:21,870
The injured one was the older brother.

280
00:13:21,870 --> 00:13:22,720
But he carried

281
00:13:22,720 --> 00:13:24,650
his younger brother's student ID.

282
00:13:24,790 --> 00:13:25,600
I remember

283
00:13:25,910 --> 00:13:27,640
he was a very upright young man.

284
00:13:28,000 --> 00:13:28,870
What a pity.

285
00:13:29,440 --> 00:13:30,510
It's impossible, doctor.

286
00:13:30,510 --> 00:13:31,150
Impossible.

287
00:13:31,150 --> 00:13:32,510
You must have made a mistake!

288
00:13:32,510 --> 00:13:33,910
He—he couldn't have gone blind.

289
00:13:33,910 --> 00:13:34,650
If he's blind,

290
00:13:34,650 --> 00:13:35,440
what will happen to his future?

291
00:13:35,440 --> 00:13:36,320
